RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 88. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race at a mile or over since March 13 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20 ,000 (Claiming races for $16,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOT DAME moved clear to set the pace inside on or just off the rail, extended the margin over the field along with the nearest pursuer past the half-mile marker, came out a bit turning for home, was challenged and just headed near the eighth pole, drifted out a bit in the stretch but dug in to regain control and edge clear. SEAWARD stalked the winner two to three wide early, followed that one to widen on the rest of the field late up the backstretch, drifted out a bit in upper stretch, bid near the furlong marker putting a very short head in front briefly but was only second best. DIALED INNA shifted in from three to two wide on the first turn and nearer the rail for the run up the backstretch in pursuit mid-pack, lost ground late up the backstretch, began to pick it up on the far turn while gradually shifting out five wide by the top of the stretch, ran on evenly. RONAN bobbled very slightly at the start, settled outside a runner at the rear two wide into the first turn, moved to the rail on the far turn, was never able to menace the leaders. JULIAISON bobbled ever so slightly at the start, chased from outside three to four wide, dropped back and faded. A REAL HERO was just a bit rank into the first turn racing inside, was not a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside-2path, drift out str, headed 1/8, dug in

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked winner 2-3w, drift bit str, bid 1/8, outkicked, 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference by condition eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR NATION eased back and tucked in three then two wide on the first turn off the leaders, pulled against the rider keenly past the five-eighths to advance inside just off the leader, switched out at the half and went three to four wide on the far turn coming five deep to the top of the stretch, gained steadily and forged clear through the final sixteenth. MINNESOTA MOON set the pace racing on or just off the rail, faced pressure up the backstretch and into the far turn, was clear coming to mid-stretch but challenged at that juncture and outkicked. GO BERTI stumbled at the start, was caught five wide into the first turn then moved in a bit, continued racing off the pace two to three wide on the far turn, moved a bit nearer the rail in the stretch and fought on to secure show honors while no match for the top pair. ANCIENT MAN lacked early speed bringing up the rear, moved out to be four wide into the far turn fanned six deep into upper stretch, thereupon shifted in to be three wide and outside a rival and kicked on mildly. MINING CAMP moved forward four wide on the first turn and rapidly advanced early up the backstretch to press outside two to three wide, floated wider for the drive still in range but weakened thereafter. CHERRY ORCHARD raced up close early two wide, began to drop back steadily, was not persevered with in the lane and walked off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside-2p, pressured, outkicked

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LATIN CASINO was coaxed forward at the start, set the pace, saved ground on the turn along the rail, shook off rivals and drew clear in the stretch under steady handling. RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEMPHIS PRAYER was reserved inside off the early pace, came out beginning on the far turn and was about five wide with aim in upper stretch, lugged in while taking the lead in mid-stretch, dueled late and prevailed. ARROW STRIKE raced in back of the leading pair off the rail in the two to three path, began to advanced leaving the far turn coming into upper stretch four deep then shifted back in, ground on to bid inside in mid-stretch but was outfinished. GO FOR IT moved forward outside the leader early up the backstretch to prompt the pace, let that one run on with the lead then again advanced to apply pressure taking a narrow lead early on the far turn, drifted out into the stretch, dueled, kept on to get show honors. OVER CALENDARED set the pace shifting in, was pressured up the backstretch, dueled in the stretch while drifting out, was in tight nearing the sixteenth pole as a rival came in, missed show. IZEONDEC was caught four to five wide in the early going, moved nearer inside to save some ground on the far turn into upper stretch, came out at that juncture and ran on. FATHER PATRICK was forced out entering the first turn, raced four then three wide on that bend, continued three to four wide on the far turn, altered inside a rival in upper stretch, was unable to menace. TEA WITH LEMON appeared to clip then jump over a rivals' heels and outward nearly unseating the rider heading into the first turn, keenly moved forward three wide soon after, went three to five wide late and came up empty. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION THE HALF-MILE AND THREE-QUARTER-MILE FRACTIONS WERE UNAVAILABLE.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHERE'D THE DAY GO switched outside the leader into the first turn, moved forward on that one three wide to press the pace beginning near the three-quarter pole, took over outside the three-eighths, was clear into upper stretch and kept to the task. POWERFUL MAN was forwardly-placed stalking four deep, kept on evenly but was second best. FLASHY RICHIE shifted in racing mid-pack two to three wide, ran on, held show honors. DEORA STORE saved ground inside early racing just off the leaders mid-pack, came out two then three wide on the far turn, needed more in the lane. ZARMAE settled near but just off the rail racing toward the back, swung out turning for home then angled outside foes eight deep in upper stretch and improved position. SON OF GRACE raced up close but off the leaders five to six wide, kept on one-paced. CHOCOLATE BUNNY moved clear and shifted in to the two path to set the pace, faced some pressure early up the backstretch, moved clear again midway up the backstretch, was overtaken on the far turn, began to drop back and angled out five wide at the head of the lane, faded thereafter. GENOMIC broke a step slowly, was outpaced at the rear, not persevered with late and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EMPIRE BUILDER had the early lead two to three wide, eased off a rival content to press outside two to three wide, moved clear at will leaving the backstretch, widened in the lane. SULLY'S BARRON was a bit hard to load, raced toward the back going in the two to three path on the turn and was not a factor.
